{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use British English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = | image = | country = England | fullname = Henry James William Wheeler | nickname = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1840|3|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Gibraltar]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1908|10|29|1840|3|27|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Westminster]], [[London]], England | heightft = | heightinch = | batting = | bowling = | role = | family = | club1 = [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]] | year1 = 1864 | clubnumber1 = | deliveries = balls | columns = 1 | column1 = [[First-class cricket|FC]] | matches1 = 1 | runs1 = 44 | bat avg1 = 22.00 | 100s/50s1 = –/– | top score1 = 27 | deliveries1 = – | wickets1 = – | bowl avg1 = – | fivefor1 = – | tenfor1 = – | best bowling1 = – | catches/stumpings1 = 1/– | date = 27 November | year = 2010 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/22886.html Cricinfo }}
'''Henry James William Wheeler''' (27 March 1840 – 29 October 1908) was an English [[cricket]]er. Wheeler's [[batsman (cricket)|batting]] and [[bowling (cricket)|bowling]] styles are unknown. He was born on [[Gibraltar]].
Wheeler made his one and only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] appearance for [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]] in 1864 against [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]] at the [[Royal Brunswick Ground]] in [[Brighton]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/33/33768/First-Class_Matches.html First-Class Matches played by Henry Wheeler]</ref> In this match he scored 44 runs in two innings, with a high score of 27 and a [[batting average]] of 22.00, while in the field he took a single [[catch (cricket)|catch]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/33/33768/f_Batting_by_Team.html First-class Batting and Fielding For Each Team by Henry Wheeler]</ref>
