{{Infobox football biography | name = Jeff Nzokira | image = | image_size = | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1987|10|24}} | birth_place = [[Burundi]] | height = {{height|m=1.80}} | currentclub = [[AS Ali Sabieh Djibouti Télécom|Djibouti Télécom]] | clubnumber = | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 200x–2012 | clubs1 = [[Vital'O FC]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2012– | clubs2 = [[AS Ali Sabieh Djibouti Télécom|Djibouti Télécom]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = | clubs3 = | caps3 = | goals3 = | nationalyears1 = 2011– | nationalteam1 = [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]] | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 = | manageryears2 = | managerclubs2 = | manageryears3 = | managerclubs3 = | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
'''Jeff Nzokira''' (born 24 October 1987) is a [[Burundi]]an footballer who currently plays for the [[AS Ali Sabieh Djibouti Télécom|Djibouti Télécom]] as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].
==Career== He played for the [[Vital'O FC]] and [[AS Ali Sabieh Djibouti Télécom|Djibouti Télécom]]. He made his international debut for [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]] in 2011.<ref>{{NFT player|id=41285|accessdate=}}</ref>
