{{infobox country at games | NOC = MLT | NOCname = [[Malta Olympic Committee]] | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.nocmalta.org }} | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Malta|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Malta|competition=Winter Olympics|begin_year=2014|end_year= }} | seealso = }} '''[[Malta]]''' has competed in 15 [[Summer Olympic Games]] and 1 [[Winter Olympic Games]].
As of the London 2012 Olympic Games no Maltese competitor has won an Olympic medal. However shooter [[William Chetcuti]] (who has won World Championship events) missed the [[Double Trap]] Shooting final in 2004, 2008 and 2012 by a relatively slim margin. In 2004 and 2008 Chetcuti was tied for 6th (the required placing to enter the final), but lost at a tie breaker. [[Elise Pellegrin]] is the first Winter Olympian to represent the country, in [[2014 Winter Olympics]] in [[Sochi]].<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|date=30 January 2013|title=Young skier to compete for Malta in next Alpine Ski World Cup|url=http://m.maltatoday.com.mt/newsdetails/sports/Young-skier-to-compete-for-Malta-in-next-Alpine-Ski-World-Cup-20130130|newspaper=[[Malta Today]]|location=|publisher=|accessdate=11 January 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111220026/http://m.maltatoday.com.mt/newsdetails/sports/Young-skier-to-compete-for-Malta-in-next-Alpine-Ski-World-Cup-20130130|archivedate=11 January 2014|df=}}</ref>
The Maltese Olympic Committee was formed in 1928 and recognized by the IOC in 1936.
