'''Mohiddin Mohamed Kulmiye''' (born 1958) is a [[marathon runner]] who competed internationally for [[Somalia]].
Kulmiye competed at the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] in [[Los Angeles]] and the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Seoul]], in the 1984 [[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics – Men's 10000 metres|10000 metres]] he finished 11th in his heat so didn't advance to the final, in 1988 he competed in the [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics – Men's marathon|marathon]] and finished in 91st position.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ku/mohiddin-mohamed-kulmiye-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Olympic Games 1988|url=http://www.olympicgamesmarathon.com/olympiad1988.php|website=olympicgamesmarathon.com|accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref>
