{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox Newspaper | name = Mundo Deportivo | image = MundoDeportivo.jpg | caption = | type = National daily sports newspaper | format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] | foundation = {{start date and age|1906}} | ceased publication = | price = | owners = Grupo Godó | publisher = | editor = Santi Nolla | language = Spanish | political = | circulation = | headquarters = [[Barcelona]] | sister newspapers = ''[[La Vanguardia]]'' | ISSN = | website = [http://www.mundodeportivo.com/ mundodeportivo.com] }} '''''Mundo Deportivo''''' ({{IPA-es|ˈmundo ðepoɾˈtiβo}};{{efn|In isolation, ''Deportivo'' is pronounced {{IPA-es|depoɾˈtiβo|}}.}} meaning ''Sports World'' in English) is a [[Spanish language|Spanish]] nationwide daily sports newspaper published in [[Barcelona]] .
==History and profile== ''Mundo Deportivo'' was first published on 1 February 1906,<ref>[http://hemeroteca.elmundodeportivo.es/edition.html?bd=01&bm=02&by=1906&x=19&y=12 Copy of the first edition of "Mundo Deportivo", 1 February 1906]</ref> as a weekly newspaper, and since 1929 daily. It is the oldest sports newspaper still published in Spain, and the second one in Europe, after the Italian ''[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]'' which was founded in 1896.<ref>International Association of Sports Newspapers (IASN), [http://www.press-iasn.org/members/members.html Association Members]</ref>
It is published in Barcelona and is owned by ''Grupo Godó''.<ref name=dav>{{cite journal|author1=Enric Castelló|author2=David Domingo|title=Spanish media facing new media: a challenge to journalists?|journal=International Journal of Iberian Studies|date=2005|volume=18|issue=3|url=http://eds.a.ebscohost.com/ehost/pdfviewer/pdfviewer?sid=c38d19e1-7bac-4754-8a34-a4d204a334c8%40sessionmgr4002&vid=0&hid=4210|accessdate=3 December 2014}}</ref> The group also owns ''[[La Vanguardia]]''.<ref name=dav/>
''Mundo Deportive'' focuses primarily on the performances of [[FC Barcelona]], but also covers the Spanish basketball league ([[Asociación de Clubs de Baloncesto|ACB]]), [[Grand Prix motorcycle racing]] and [[Formula One]] car racing, amongst others.
Both ''Mundo Deportivo'' and ''[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]'' are the predominant sources of sports news in [[Catalonia]].
