{{EngvarB|date=October 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Malay name|Nur Ikhwan|Othman}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Nur Ikhwan | fullname = Mohammad Nurikhwan bin Othman | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|01|15}} | birth_place = [[Brunei]] | currentclub = [[DPMM FC]] | clubnumber = 19 | position = [[Midfield]] | height = {{height|m=1.72}} | youthyears1 = 2010–2012 | youthclubs1 = [[Brunei Sports School|Sports School]] | years1 = 2010–2011 | clubs1 = [[Brunei Youth Team]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2012–2015 | clubs2 = [[Indera SC]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[DPMM FC]] | caps3 = 30| goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2012–2014 | nationalteam1 = [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 11 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | nationalyears2 = 2012–2013 | nationalteam2 = [[Brunei national under-23 football team|Brunei U23]] | nationalcaps2 = 5 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2012– | nationalteam3 = [[Brunei national football team|Brunei]] | nationalcaps3 = 6 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | pcupdate = 16 August 2018 | ntupdate = 11 September 2018 }}
'''Mohammad Nurikhwan bin Othman''' (born 15 January 1993) is a [[Brunei]]an [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] for [[DPMM FC]].
Nur Ikhwan attended Brunei's [[Brunei Sports School|Sports School]] as a youngster and progressed enough to be a regular in the national youth team side that played in the [[Brunei Premier League]] II in [[2009–10 Brunei Premier League|2010]] and [[2011 Brunei Premier League|2011]].<ref>{{cite web |title=PIP dip into fountain of youth|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sport-national/2010/03/27/pip-dip-fountain-youth|date=27 May 2010|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref> After the creation of the Brunei National Football League (precursor to the [[Brunei Super League]]) by the newly formed [[National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|NFABD]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Let football league begin!|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2011/12/03/let-football-league-begin|date=3 December 2011|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref> the young prodigy chose [[Indera SC]] as his club, becoming league champions in [[2012–13 Brunei Super League|2012-13]] and [[2014 Brunei Super League|2014]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Indera SC repeat as champs|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2014/09/03/indera-sc-repeat-champs|date=3 September 2014|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>
Nur Ikhwan signed for professional side [[DPMM FC]] of the [[S.League]] in 2016 and made his debut in a 3–2 loss to [[Albirex Niigata Singapore FC|Albirex Niigata (S)]] on 13 February.<ref>{{cite web |title=DPMM FC start season|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2016/02/13/dpmm-fc-start-season|date=13 February 2016|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=15 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=S.League.com - Match Details|url=http://www.sleague.com/match-details/?id=SL/16-0001|date=13 February 2016|publisher=S.League|accessdate=15 February 2016}}</ref>
==International career== Nur Ikhwan played with the [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei Under-21s]] in the [[2012 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy]] when the home side emerged as victors. He played every game and scored in the semi-final against [[Myanmar national under-19 football team|Myanmar]]. He was made captain for the [[2014 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy|2014 edition]] although his side failed to defend the title.
Nur Ikhwan's full international career began when he played the first half in a friendly against [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]] on 26 September 2012.<ref>{{cite web |title=Hat-Trick Irfan Bachdim Hantam Brunei Darussalam|url=http://www.goal.com/id-ID/news/1387/nasional/2012/09/27/3405055/hat-trick-irfan-bachdim-hantam-brunei-darussalam|date=27 September 2012|publisher=Goal.com|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref> He played for the Wasps in the [[2012 AFF Championship qualification|2012]], [[2014 AFF Championship qualification|2014]] and [[2018 AFF Championship qualification|2018]] [[AFF Suzuki Cup]] qualifying rounds.
